In a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings), combine @farro{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and @water{2 1/2%cups} (5 cups for 4). Bring to a boil and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> If you end up with any excess stock, pour it out. Alternatively, if stock evaporates before farro is done, add a splash of water.

Meanwhile, wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3}. Dice @roma tomato{1}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}.

Rub @corn on the cob{1} all over with a drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}. Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add corn and cook, rotating frequently, until some kernels are charred, ~{7-9%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to cool slightly. Wipe out pan.

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add @pepitas{1%oz}, @water{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4 servings), @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of @chipotle powder{pinch} and @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring, until pepitas are coated and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Squeeze juice from half the lime into a #large bowl{}. Whisk in @sour cream{2%tbsp}, 1 TBSP olive oil (2 TBSP for 4), half the lime zest, @chipotle powder{1/4%tsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). Add water, 1 tsp at a time, until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{}.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4), remaining lime zest, @salt{} and @pepper{} into farro; divide between bowls. Slice corn kernels off cob; discard cob. Add corn, @arugula{2%oz}, tomato, pepitas, and as many radishes as you like to bowl with dressing. Toss to combine. Season generously with salt. Top farro with arugula mixture and @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.